4 (c) A minor's right to consult with a parent or legal guardian under
5 subsection (b) of this section shall not be waived by the minor.
6 (d) Except as provided in subsection (e) of this section, any
7 statements obtained from a minor in violation of this section shall be
8 inadmissible in a delinquency or criminal proceeding unless the prosecuting
